cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with performance analysis and power optimization of wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of stochastic network calculus and queuing theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The focus on industrial applications and process automation suggests that the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The consideration of channel heterogeneity and the use of simulation studies suggest that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories, respectively.
